"```sql\nSELECT Patient.ID, Patient.SEX, Patient.Birthday\nFROM Patient\nJOIN Laboratory ON Patient.ID = Laboratory.ID\nWHERE Laboratory.UN = 29;\n```\n\nThis SQL query selects the ID, sex, and birthday of patients from the `Patient` table who have a urea nitrogen (UN) level of 29, which is considered just within the borderline of passing according to the provided evidence. The query joins the `Patient` and `Laboratory` tables using the foreign key relationship `Laboratory.ID = Patient.ID`."